Social Studies, including history and geography, curriculum will be listed on this page.
At this time, in no particular order. Editing, arrange, and extra details will be added
over time. Some curricula mentioned cover more than just Social Studies, others are places
to find particular lesson plans. Research and decide what is best for your own individual
needs.


Story of the World, Elementary and Middle School, also used as the text of other history curricula.
Pandia Press History Quest, Elementary and Middle School
Pandia Press History Odyssey, Middle - High School
Pandia Press Modern History Bridge, Grades 3-7
Core Knowledge Online - curriculum available for K-8
  https://www.coreknowledge.org/history-geography/

Build Your Library - Charlotte Mason inspired/ literature based approach to homeschooling
  https://buildyourlibrary.com/
Blossom and Root - Charlotte Mason and Waldorf inspired
  https://www.blossomandroot.com/
Georgia Virtual Learning
  https://gavirtuallearning.org/ga-digital-curriculum/free-resources/
Lesson Plans on the topic of Racism from Human Rights Educators USA
  https://hreusa.org/hre-library/topics/racism/lesson-plans/

Bookshark - Is the "secular" arm of Sonlight, which is a religous literature based curriculum.
The Good and the Beautiful - this is a religious infused curriculum that has some free
  options. Especially during the 2020-2022 push for homeschooling they wanted to keep
  homeschooling affordable and accessible to as many families as possible.
